= heel
Al Idian <al.idian@acm.org>
:description: Disable the macOS keyboard

`heel` disables the macOS keyboard, including special keys like brightness and volume.
Press ctrl-c to re-enable it.
Please note this software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind.

Usage:

1. Clone this repo.
2. Grant Accessibility permission to your terminal in System Settings > Privacy & Security > Accessibility.
3. (Optional) Set permissions and view the help text.

+
[source,bash]
----
chmod 700 ./heel
./heel --help
----

4. Run `heel`.

+
[source,bash]
----
./heel
----
